HEADWORD: low-toned
<hw>low-toned</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>relatively low in volume; soft;
-- of sound; <as>as, making <ex>low-toned</ex> noises with their mouths
that went as an undercurrent of sound</as>. Opposite of
<ant>loud</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> low, subdued, soft.</syn>⟦br⟧
